---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Chaos Studies - Field Bureau + Werkstatt"
  description="Terms of Service for Chaos Studies app"
  gradientOverlay="linear-gradient(to bottom, #1a1a1a, #0a0a0a)"
>
  <div class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col">

    <!-- Breadcrumb Navigation -->
    <nav class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-6">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-2 text-sm text-white/80 drop-shadow-lg">
        <a href="/chaos-studies" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Chaos Studies</a>
        <span class="text-white/40">/</span>
        <span class="text-white">Terms of Service</span>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="relative z-10 px-6 md:px-12 py-12 flex-1">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

        <!-- Header -->
        <div class="text-center mb-16 animate-fade-in-up" style="opacity: 0;">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-light text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Terms of Service
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-white/70 drop-shadow-lg">
            Chaos Studies
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/50 mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
            Last updated: January 26, 2026
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Content Sections -->
        <div class="space-y-8 animate-fade-in-up" style="animation-delay: 200ms; opacity: 0;">

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              By downloading, installing, or using Chaos Studies ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">2. Description of Service</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              Chaos Studies is an application for iOS, macOS, and Playdate that provides interactive visualizations of strange attractors—mathematical patterns that emerge from chaotic dynamical systems. The App provides:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Real-time 3D visualization of nine different strange attractors</li>
              <li>Interactive controls (touch, crank, motion)</li>
              <li>Generative audio synthesis (iOS/macOS)</li>
              <li>Light and dark display modes</li>
              <li>Motion parallax effects</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">3. System Requirements</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App requires:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li><strong>iOS:</strong> iOS 15.0 or later</li>
              <li><strong>macOS:</strong> macOS 12.0 (Monterey) or later</li>
              <li><strong>Playdate:</strong> Playdate handheld console with current firmware</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">4. Privacy and Data</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App operates with minimal data collection:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>No personal data is transmitted to external servers</li>
              <li>Motion sensor data is used only for real-time parallax effects</li>
              <li>All settings and configurations are stored locally on your device</li>
              <li>See our <a href="/chaos-studies-privacy" class="text-white underline hover:text-white/80">Privacy Policy</a> for complete details</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">5. Permissions</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App may request the following permissions:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li><strong>Motion & Accelerometer (iOS):</strong> Optional permission for parallax effects</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mt-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              You can revoke these permissions at any time through your device's system settings.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App, including its design, code, visualizations, and audio, is the intellectual property of Field Bureau & Werkstatt LLC. The mathematical equations for strange attractors are in the public domain; our specific implementation and presentation are protected.
            </p>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              You may not copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works based on the App without explicit written permission.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from the use of the App, including but not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Device compatibility issues</li>
              <li>Visual or audio playback issues</li>
              <li>Battery consumption</li>
              <li>Data loss or corruption</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">8. Health Considerations</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              The App displays animated visual content. If you are sensitive to flashing lights or motion, please use the App with caution. We recommend taking breaks during extended use.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">9. User Responsibilities</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">
              Users are responsible for:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/80 leading-relaxed space-y-2 drop-shadow-lg">
              <li>Ensuring device compatibility</li>
              <li>Using the App in accordance with these Terms</li>
              <li>Managing audio volume at safe levels</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">10. Updates and Changes</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              We may update the App and these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of any changes. Updates will be distributed through the respective app stores.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">11. Termination</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              You may stop using the App at any time by uninstalling it from your device. These Terms will remain in effect until terminated by either party.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium text-white mb-4 drop-shadow-lg">12. Contact Information</h2>
            <p class="text-white/80 leading-relaxed drop-shadow-lg">
              If you have questions about these Terms or the App, please contact us through the App Store or at <a href="/support" class="text-white underline hover:text-white/80">our support page</a>.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="border border-white/30 rounded-xl p-6 backdrop-blur-sm bg-white/10">
            <p class="text-sm text-white/70 drop-shadow-lg">
              These Terms of Service are effective as of January 26, 2026. By using Chaos Studies, you acknowledge that you have read and understood these Terms and agree to be bound by them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Footer with black background -->
  <footer class="bg-black py-8 px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-center text-white/30 text-xs tracking-wide">
        <span class="font-semibold">Field Bureau + Werkstatt</span>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        © {new Date().getFullYear()} Field Bureau & Werkstatt LLC. All rights reserved.
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
